Unit Tests

Purpose: Isolated unit tests for individual classes and methods.

What belongs here:
- Service unit tests (TAuthService, TUserService, etc.)
- Repository unit tests with mocked database connections
- Validator unit tests with various input scenarios
- DTO serialization and deserialization tests
- Helper class method tests (THelperJSON, THelperString, etc.)
- RTTI routing resolution tests (THelperCore, TClassHelper)

Test framework: DUnitX (recommended) or DUnit.
Each test file should map to a single unit under test.
Tests must not require a running server or live database.

